all the styles would be included between the <styles> </styles> at the top of the page

principal styles:
color: 
font-size:
font-family:    //// if we import a font family we need to use a second font if the first one was unavailable. Example:

font-family: "imported font", generic font;

width:

Borders have properties like style, color and width:
border-color:
border-width:
border-style:
border-radious: would be in px to square shape or in percentage for a circular shape

Use and id attribute to style an element:

Note that inside your style element, you always reference classes by putting a . in front of their names.
You always reference ids by putting a # in front of their names.


